•  Three-dimensional sculptural and cartographic works;

•  Tests;

•  Toys, dolls, and games;

•  Useful articles; and

•  Works originally published as part of a collective work.

Special Relief

The Copyright Office is authorized to grant special relief from deposit requirements in appropriate
circumstances. All requests for special relief must be made in writing. You must state the specific
reason(s) why you cannot submit the deposit required and what you will submit instead of the
required deposit. The Office will evaluate your request upon receipt.

--- PAGE BREAK ---

Request for special relief may be made either in the “Note to the Copyright Office” field of the

online application or by mail to the following address:

Associate Register of Copyrights and
Director of Registration Policy and Practice
U.S. Copyright Office
P.O. Box 70400
Washington, DC 20024-0400

For more information about special relief, see chapter 1500, section 1508.8, of the Compendium.

